sources.description:
Black Rose - In the film "Black Rose," Russian Police Major Vladimir Kazatov is invited to Los Angeles to assist local law enforcement in investigating a series of brutal murders. The victims are young women, and the trail leads to a mysterious serial killer operating on the streets of Hollywood. The LAPD faces difficulties as the killerâ€™s methods are extremely sophisticated and cruel, leaving minimal evidence behind.

Kazatov, known for his resourcefulness and determination, begins the investigation alongside a local detective. Cultural differences complicate their collaboration, but the major's experience helps uncover new leads on the killer. It turns out that the crimes are linked to underground organizations operating on both sides of the ocean.

Time is running out as the killer becomes bolder, attempting to erase all traces and evade justice. Kazatov and his partner must act quickly to stop the maniac before he strikes again in the heart of Hollywood.
